{"word":"κλύδων","slug":"κλύδων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κλύδων</b></el> <el>(κλύ˘δων, ωνος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κλύζω'><el>κλύζω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a wave, billow</i>, and collectively <i>surf</i> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>κλ. κακῶν</el> <i>a sea</i> of troubles, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>κλ. ξυμφορᾶς</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>κλ. ἔφιππος</el> <i>a flood</i> of horsemen, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}